{
  "texts": [
    "First, we compute the EE for both the original and dual systems using anisotropic CTMRG with 4 × 4 and 2 × 2 unit cells, respectively [84].",
    "Kinks in the EE effectively signal phase boundaries, including BKT transitions where analyzing both the original and dual systems proves useful [30,35].",
    "Z q symmetry-breaking is detected via the non-zero Z q order parameter ⟨e iθ ⟩ at a representative CTMRG site.",
    "The Z 2 NM order is identified using the nematic order parameter:κ = 1 4 ⟨cos (θ i -θ i+x) + cos (θ i+ŷ -θ i+x+ŷ) -cos (θ i -θ i+ŷ) - cos (θ i+x -θ i+x+ŷ)⟩.This quantity approaches κ ∼ ±1 deep within the nematic phases, as shown in Fig. 1(e).",
    "I, we summarize all the phases present in the system classified according to their symmetry properties."
  ]
}